329,IssuesEvent,2018-02-23 21:39:54+00:00,11737385,Dav1dde/glad,255721,Dav1dde,,,closed,Overallocation in function get_exts(),"[{'id': 423709352, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Dav1dde/glad/labels/C', 'name': 'C', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}, {'id': 49792957, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Dav1dde/glad/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 512948486, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Dav1dde/glad/labels/glad1', 'name': 'glad1', 'color': 'e99695', 'default': False}, {'id': 417773771, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Dav1dde/glad/labels/glad2', 'name': 'glad2', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],2,"There seems to be an oversized allocation in ```get_exts()``` at glad/lang/c/loader/gl.py, see line 57:
```char *local_str = (char*)malloc((len+1) * sizeof(*exts_i));```
The variable ```exts_i``` is of type ```const char **```, so ```sizeof (*exts_i)``` is equivalent to ```sizeof (const char *)```, but we just need ```sizeof (char)```. I would suggest to replace the line in question with:
```char *local_str = (char*)malloc((len+1) * sizeof(*local_str));```",{},{}
