748,IssuesEvent,2017-03-01 05:37:14+00:00,77868600,benjaminp/six,219470,benjaminp,,,closed,Six doesn't provide a solution for the commands module,"[{'id': 510582194, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/benjaminp/six/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 510582255, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/benjaminp/six/labels/major', 'name': 'major', 'color': 'ededed', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Originally reported by: **Anonymous**

----------------------------------------

Older versions of Python had the [commands module](https://docs.python.org/2/library/commands.html).  This was deprecated in 2.6 and removed in 3.0, with the methods being moved to subprocess.  Six should allow something like

```
#!python
from six.moves import commands

commands.getstatusoutput()
commands.getoutput()
commands.getstatus()
```

----------------------------------------
- Bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/gutworth/six/issue/138
",{},{}
