2800,IssuesEvent,2018-05-10 00:18:05+00:00,68545771,MichaelAquilina/S4,14123345,digitaltommy,,,opened,.syncignore unable to sync specific file extensions only.,[],[],0,"Hi,

Either my .syncignore (.gitignore style) file below is incorrect, or it is currently not supported within s4.

I'm trying to ignore syncing of all files, and then negate the ignore for certain file extensions, is this possible? I've started doing this as I experienced a large amount of random .pyc files etc that were losing their sync with the s3 bucket. I thought I would cover all bases and selectively allow certain file extensions or specific files as I require.

.syncignore
```
# Stop everything being synced
*
    
# Allow sub directories 
!*/                
                    
# Except syncignore
!.syncignore                               
                                           
# Add file types below that we want to sync
!*.py  
!*.xls 
!*.xlsx
!*.txt                                                            
!*.sh
```

Thanks,

Tom",{},{}
