3570,IssuesEvent,2015-05-25 07:36:33+00:00,3247274,niwinz/django-jinja,843689,niwinz,,,closed,"django-jinja 1.4.3 gives Bound error functions (ex., ModelForm)",[],[],1,"The following is with django-jinja 1.4.3 and django1.8.2. Compare the two runs between a template loading the default Django template language and the other using Jinja2 via django-jinja:

```
(jinja2test) [bafflermeal@kdev05:/apps/sites/jinja2test/top]15> cat cases/templates/cases/label_tag_example.html
{% for field in NEW_CASE_FORM %}
<div class=""fieldWrapper"">
{{ field.errors }} {{ field.label_tag }} {{ field }}
</div>
{% endfor %}

(jinja2test) [bafflermeal@kdev05:/apps/sites/jinja2test/top]16> cat cases/templates/cases/label_tag_example.jinja
{% for field in NEW_CASE_FORM %}
<div class=""fieldWrapper"">
{{ field.errors }} {{ field.label_tag }} {{ field }}
</div>
{% endfor %}

(jinja2test) [bafflermeal@kdev05:/apps/sites/jinja2test/top]17>


>>> from cases.models import Case
>>> from cases.forms import CaseForm
>>> from django.http import HttpResponse, HttpResponseRedirect
>>> from django.template import loader, RequestContext, Template

>>> context = { 'NEW_CASE_FORM': CaseForm() }

>>> template = loader.get_template('cases/label_tag_example.html')
>>> template.render(context=context)
'\n<div class=""fieldWrapper"">\n <label for=""id_title"">Title:</label> <input id=""id_title"" maxlength=""120"" name=""title"" type=""text"" />\n</div>\n\n<div class=""fieldWrapper"">\n <label for=""id_agent"">Agent:</label> <input id=""id_agent"" name=""agent"" type=""text"" />\n</div>\n\n'

>>> template = loader.get_template('cases/label_tag_example.jinja',using='django_jinja')
>>> template.render(context=context)
'\n<div class=""fieldWrapper"">\n &lt;bound method BoundField.label_tag of &lt;django.forms.forms.BoundField object at 0x2b557e9e8390&gt;&gt; <input id=""id_title"" maxlength=""120"" name=""title"" type=""text"" />\n</div>\n\n<div class=""fieldWrapper"">\n &lt;bound method BoundField.label_tag of &lt;django.forms.forms.BoundField object at 0x2b557e9e8400&gt;&gt; <input id=""id_agent"" name=""agent"" type=""text"" />\n</div>\n'

```

Note that the template render using the same context with `using='django_jinja' ` yields messages such as: `bound method BoundField.label_tag of <django.forms.forms.BoundField object at 0x2b557e9e8390>` when referencing some items in a `ModelForm` after `.is_valid()` has been run. The same code doesn't appear to cause any issues with the Django template language loader.

This error comes from trying to print `{{ field.label_tag }}` in the example.
",{},{}
