4639,IssuesEvent,2018-07-01 18:21:49+00:00,30582779,warner/magic-wormhole,27146,warner,,,opened,failures on py3.7,[],[],0,"Python3.7.0 was released just a few days ago. I'm seeing test-suite failures when I add `py37` to the `tox.ini` list.

One of them is because `tempfile.SpooledTemporaryFile` doesn't fully implement the `IOBase` abstract class (https://bugs.python.org/issue26175), specifically it doesn't forward calls to`f.seekable()` down into the various other filetypes that it wraps (it starts out wrapping a in-memory `BytesIO` object, but switches to a real on-disk file once the size grows above some threshold). This wasn't a problem in python3.7.0a4 (the most recent 'nightly' that travis tested) because no other code cares, but late in the 3.7 cycle the `zipfile` module was changed to care about the `.seekable` property, now we get an `AttributeError` when zipfile tries to reference `file.seekable`.

I'm adding a workaround for that to `cmd_send.py` in the `build_offer()` function by just adding a `seekable()` method to the SpooledTemporaryFile if there wasn't one there already. It always returns True: as best I can tell all the wrapped file types are always seekable anyways. `cmd_receive.py` needs a similar workaround.

Unfortunately neither Travis-CI nor Appveyor have been updated to include py3.7 yet.
",{},{}
