4947,IssuesEvent,2018-02-03 22:01:08+00:00,54834492,ResidentMario/missingno,3466341,ResidentMario,,,closed,Include smaller example data for users to follow along (and for future tests),[],[],4,"This package is meant to tackle the visualization tasks of large data sets, and the provided examples are fantastic for demonstrating the utter complexity that users may face. I'm especially glad to see that you have posted [examples of how you munged the data](https://github.com/ResidentMario/motor-vehicle-collisions/blob/master/NYPD%20Motor%20Vehicle%20Collisions.ipynb). This is quite valuable to fair-weather Python users such as myself. 👍 

However, in order to follow along, users must start by downloading all 1M+ rows (and growing!) of the NYPDMVC data set. 😿 My suggestion would be to include a small subset of these data in the package (I believe you can specify the location with `package_data` in your setup file).",{},{}
4961,IssuesEvent,2018-05-23 21:46:41+00:00,892815,achillean/shodan-python,373864,achillean,,,opened,Store stream data in chunks,[],[],0,"Provide a new parameter in the CLI to store the data from the firehose in specified file size chunks. For example, the following command stores information in the **firehose-data** directory and once a file size gets above 100MB it creates a new data file in the directory:

    shodan stream --datadir firehose-data/ --chunk=100M",{},{}
4964,IssuesEvent,2016-02-08 20:13:54+00:00,30379674,adamchainz/django-mysql,857609,adamchainz,,,closed,"Smart iterator output ""Finished"" message should say how long it took","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/adamchainz/django-mysql/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,It would be nice after large data migrations to know how long it took. The `Finished!` message could easily be extended with the time taken.,{},{}
4972,IssuesEvent,2016-05-14 11:01:52+00:00,30379674,adamchainz/django-mysql,857609,adamchainz,,,closed,Error in JSONField if multiple databases are used including non MySQL databses,[],[],6,"Hi, I have a project where I'm using two databases: a MySQL database and a MS SQL Server database.
If I don't use a JSONField everything works fine. But when I try to migrate a model using a JSONField i get the following error:

`File ""/home/......../virtualenvs/seta_fs/lib/python3.4/site-packages/django_mysql/models/fields/json.py"", line 79, in _check_mysql_version
    not connections[db].is_mariadb and
AttributeError: 'DatabaseWrapper' object has no attribute 'is_mariadb'`
 
It appears that the function _check_mysql_version loops all the database configured assuming that the attribute ""is_mariadb"" is defined. So when it checks the non MySQL database it fails.

I tried to fix this issue and I know that I should use MySQL instead of MariaDB. You can look at my attempt here:  https://github.com/marco-santamaria/django-mysql/commit/aa00dc0d200f462633b9a1528d19d78c52db6947

Do you have any advice?


Django Version: *e.g. Django 1.9.5*
Database and version used: *MariaDB 10.1.13*
Version: *Django-MySQL 1.0.8*",{},{}
