5097,IssuesEvent,2015-09-22 04:06:53+00:00,9376661,lorenzofox3/Smart-Table,3280795,huynhom,,,opened,Why $timeout improves the performance? Is it a bug with smart-table?,[],[],0,"Take this codes as example: http://plnkr.co/edit/wOOHZV?p=preview

This is the loop I am interested in:
```javascript
      var l = 100;
      for (var j = 0; j < l; j++) {
        $scope.source.push(createRandomItem());
      }
```

Try to increase that to 20000, you will notice it is really slow.
```javascript
      var l = 20000;
      for (var j = 0; j < l; j++) {
        $scope.source.push(createRandomItem());
      }
```
I found that doing it in batches with a $timeout call will largely improve the performance. But i don't understand why?. I tried to put a lot of debug point in smart-table.js but could not have any clue why? Is it a bug with smart-table where it tries to do something weird in the beginning?
```javascript
      var l = 20000;
      for (var j = 0; j < 10; j++) {
        $scope.source.push(createRandomItem());
      }
      
      $timeout(function() {
        for (var j = 10; j < l; j++) {
          $scope.source.push(createRandomItem());
        }
      }, 1);
```

Thanks
",{},{}
