5484,IssuesEvent,2017-01-20 17:39:29+00:00,79312753,tiras-j/json-cherry-pick,6816898,tiras-j,,,opened,Define a serialization spec for the index,"[{'id': 522648941, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/tiras-j/json-cherry-pick/labels/TODO', 'name': 'TODO', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]",[],0,"This might be a stretch, but I was thinking about being able to inject the index as a base64 encoded key/value pair into valid JSON. By manual injection we can ensure it exists as the first key on the blob, and when parsing we can check the key and quickly build the entire index without scanning the blob. This would of course require passing the object to be dumped through json-cherry-pick for outputting, where we would JSON serialize, scan and build index, inject index, output. Overall a fairly quick process but still some overhead.

",{},{}
