5784,IssuesEvent,2016-07-04 00:58:15+00:00,62327543,rochacbruno/import_string,1590527,felipevolpone,,,opened,Sharing some experience,[],[],0,"Hi @rochacbruno, nice work exporting this code to a new library, it's really usefull :) 

I've done done this kind of import in some projects, but using this approach: 
```python
import importlib
foopath = 'src.apis.foo.Foo'

module_name = '.'.join(foopath.split('.')[:-1]) # to get src.apis.foo
foo_module = importlib.import_module(module_name)
