6580,IssuesEvent,2018-07-17 00:30:21+00:00,1643611,daviddrysdale/python-phonenumbers,28713002,calebbredlow,,,opened,Make the __repr__ method look similar to SRE_Match's __repr__ method,[],[],0,"Instead of doing 
` def __repr__(self):
        return (unicod(""PhoneNumberMatch(start=%r, raw_string=%r, numobj=%r)"") %
                (self.start,
                 self.raw_string,
                 self.number))

    def __unicode__(self):
        return unicod(""PhoneNumberMatch [%s,%s) %s"") % (self.start, self.end, self.raw_string)`

do something similar to re.match's __repr__ method and do 
`""<phonenumbers.PhoneNumberMatch; start={}, end={}, raw_string={}>"".format(self.start, self.end, self.raw_string)`
maybe even convert the start and end into a tuple and have it be span?",{},{}
6592,IssuesEvent,2017-09-12 14:37:02+00:00,99455688,gtalarico/airtable-python-wrapper,6793716,samgdf,,,opened,Search Param,[],[],0,"How would I get the search result to be query-able?

In other words, let's say I have
`airtable.search('Name', str(List[i]))`, where i in that list is some name equivalent to some name in the airtable. I then would like to pull the information from that specific item in the airtable. I understand that search returns that, but how would I then capture specific portions, say, `data[i]['fields']['Location']` or similar?

Cheers!",{},{}
