`Field('json_string', 'json')`
The expected outcome is to have the Postgresql DB show ""json"" as the column type for that field, but it shows ""text"".

So the error comes up.
**For pg8000:**
```
ProgrammingError: (u'ERROR', u'ERROR', u'42804', u'column ""json_string__tmp"" is of type json but expression is of type text', u'You will need to rewrite or cast the expression.', u'48', u'parse_target.c', u'540', u'transformAssignedExpr', u'', u'')
```

**For psycopg2:**
```
<class 'psycopg2.ProgrammingError'>(column ""json_string__tmp"" is of type json but expression is of type text
LINE 1: UPDATE ""data_table"" SET ""json_string__tmp""=""json_string""...
                                                       ^
HINT:  You will need to rewrite or cast the expression.
)
```

Using psql commands I change that column type from ""text"" to ""json""
`ALTER TABLE test_table ALTER COLUMN json_string TYPE JSON USING json_string::JSON;`

It worked for the first restart of the server - no errors. But subsequent restarts see the column type revert to ""text"", and the above errors for pg8000 and psycopg2 comes up.

Also, it should be mentioned that the above error only appears **once** after the server is restarted. And consistently every time the server restarts, I will expect to see it once when I load any pages from the app.
",{},{}
