8490,IssuesEvent,2015-05-21 12:18:28+00:00,22947619,robotframework/SSHLibrary,12544461,gyund,574284,robotframework,opened,Support for SCP,[],[],0,"Currently, SSHLibrary uses SFTP. However, sometimes that option is not available for use. In such a case, you can run commands from the Linux terminal such as `scp somefile.txt user@192.168.1.1:` and transfer files successfully.

If I have time, I'll see if I can understand the proper and necessary placement for it in the python code, but  I came across this post which seems to indicate a different client to use with paramiko:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/250283/how-to-scp-in-python

Basically being able to choose the file transfer method for files or directories would be nice when Sending or Retrieving Files/Directories. It probably makes sense to set these up as configuration options when setting up the connection so a particular host so that none of the Keywords have to change, thus leaving the interfaces unaffected. Switching to SCP will restrict what keywords will work, but then again, that's the reason you would switch it anyway is when they won't work in the first place.",{},{}
