8578,IssuesEvent,2017-06-25 07:43:29+00:00,15670215,nephila/djangocms-blog,714711,yakky,630341,nephila,closed,Use easy_thumbnails_tags instead,"[{'id': 73542290, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nephila/djangocms-blog/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],2,"If you're willing to require easy_thumbnails 2.4.1 or higher, it now includes a fix to enable the thumbail tag to be loaded via ```{% load easy_thumbnails_tags %}``` instead of ```{% load thumbnails %}```. This fixes a namespace conflict where other 3rd party libraries have defined their own templatetag called ""thumbnails"". sorl-thumbnail is an example of such library.

For example, one of my third party apps required solr-thumbnail, which caused django-cms blog's ```{% load thumbnails %}``` to load the solr one, instead of easy_thumbnails, resulting in errors.",{},{}
