9831,IssuesEvent,2017-12-06 13:50:18+00:00,24993138,google/brotli,315413,worenga,1342004,google,opened,append to brotli compressed file,[],[],0,"Is it possible to append data to a brotli compressed file such that it is compressed automatically?

The following would work, e.g. for gzip

```
$echo 'foo' | gzip >! test.gz
$echo 'foo' | gzip >> test.gz
zcat test
foo
foo
```

While the same approach would fail using `brotli` with 

`corrupt input`
