10151,IssuesEvent,2017-06-08 12:27:29+00:00,51384572,snowplow/snowplow-python-analytics-sdk,681171,chuwy,1476001,snowplow,opened,Add option to list glacierefied folders,[],[],0,"In `list_runids` function we explicitly skip run ids that are archived on AWS Glacier, which means they will never appear in run manifest. I believe this is wrong solution as customer can restore particular folder without intention to reprocess it (let's say with PySpark job).

I propose to: 
* Add option `list_runids(include_archived=False)` to list folders archived to AWS Glacier
* Make `list_runids()`return objects of `RunId` that can hold information whether folder is archived
* Add third possible state to https://github.com/snowplow/snowplow-python-analytics-sdk/issues/29 to mark `RunId` processing was explicitly cancelled. Something like `SucceededAt`.

This should make run manifests feature able to take full control over data processing.",{},{}
