10578,IssuesEvent,2018-03-15 18:02:02+00:00,12345160,ansible/tower-cli,15368083,oatakan,1507452,ansible,opened,not able to modify groups that are created from Tower,[],[],0,"When I create a group using tower-cli, I can then modify using `tower-cli group modify`. However when I try to modify a group that is created from Tower, I get the following error:

```
tower-cli group modify 11686 --variables ""test: value""
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/usr/bin/tower-cli"", line 90, in <module>
    cli()
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/click/core.py"", line 716, in __call__
    return self.main(*args, **kwargs)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/click/core.py"", line 696, in main
    rv = self.invoke(ctx)
  File ""/usr/bin/tower-cli"", line 82, in invoke
    return super(TowerCLI, self).invoke(ctx)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/click/core.py"", line 1060, in invoke
    return _process_result(sub_ctx.command.invoke(sub_ctx))
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/click/core.py"", line 1060, in invoke
    return _process_result(sub_ctx.command.invoke(sub_ctx))
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/click/core.py"", line 889, in invoke
    return ctx.invoke(self.callback, **ctx.params)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/click/core.py"", line 534, in invoke
    return callback(*args, **kwargs)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tower_cli/conf.py"", line 327, in method_with_context_managed
    method(*args, **kwargs)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tower_cli/models/base.py"", line 311, in func
    result = method(*args, **kwargs)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tower_cli/resources/group.py"", line 200, in modify
    isid = self._get_inventory_source_id(answer)
  File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tower_cli/resources/group.py"", line 316, in _get_inventory_source_id
    return int(group['related']['inventory_source'].split('/')[-2])
KeyError: 'inventory_source'
```

This is due to the fact that **related.inventory_source** field is not added from Tower but it gets added by tower-cli. When I get the group details with tower-cli,  it's missing the field **related.inventory_source**. This issue also impacts the [tower_group](http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/tower_group_module.html) module as it uses the tower-cli library.

