10688,IssuesEvent,2015-02-23 12:48:25+00:00,7191068,Infinidat/infi.docopt_completion,11145016,con-f-use,1667528,Infinidat,opened,docopt_completion doesn't seem to honor mandatory arguments,[],[],0,"The module does not seem to fully honor mandatory backets `(-option)` and ignores commands therein.

Example code:
```python
#!/usr/bin/env python
"""""" Demonstration of docopt_completion not honoring exclusives.

Usage:
    exhon.py --help
    exhon.py (-c cmd)

Options:
 -h      Print help
  -c     Indicats command mode
""""""

from docopt import docopt

arguments = docopt(__doc__)
print arguments
""""""

from docopt import docopt

arguments = docopt(__doc__, version='1.0')
print arguments
```

Expected behavior in shell session:
```
confus@confusion:~/test$ exhon.py #[TAB]
-c         --help
confus@confusion:~/test$ exhon.py -c #[TAB] completes to only allowed commad:
confus@confusion:~/test$ exhon.py -c cmd
```

Actual (wrong) behavier:
```
confus@confusion:~/test$ exhon.py 
-c         cmd    --help
confus@confusion:~/test$ exhon.py -c #[TAB] gives no completion
confus@confusion:~/test$ exhon.py -c
```",{},{}
