11027,IssuesEvent,2016-11-29 15:47:44+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,3311523,mitchellstern,2374376,clab,opened,Inconsistent usage of pointers and references,[],[],0,"As it stands, most of the builder classes in `dynet/` use `Model*` in their constructors, whereas most of the builder-like classes in `examples/` use `Model&`. On the other hand, `ComputationGraph`s are largely used as references throughout the code base, whereas there are a small number of pointers (some of which are unused, as in `dynet/treelstm.h`). There's even a mismatch in the current version of `c2w.h`, where (among other issues) a `ComputationGraph*` is being used where a `ComputationGraph&` is expected by `RNNBuilder`.

I'm not sure I can speak for the internal DyNet code, but for all of the builders and example models, is there any compelling reason why we shouldn't be using references uniformly throughout? If not, I'd be happy to make a pull request to this effect for consistency.",{},{}
