11102,IssuesEvent,2017-09-27 14:25:08+00:00,58705171,opencobra/memote,2588245,cdanielmachado,2708410,opencobra,opened,Gene-Protein-Reaction associations in canonical format,[],[],0,"Probably won't get any support on this one, but here it goes anyway :)

GPR associations should be tested for biological meaning. The interpretation of boolean OR and AND operators as biological entities (isozymes and enzyme complexes) is only unambiguous if the boolean rule is encoded in a canonical format (disjunctive normal form, in this particular case).

This can be easily tested with the *is_dnf* function from sympy:

http://docs.sympy.org/latest/modules/logic.html#sympy.logic.boolalg.is_dnf
",{},{}
