11134,IssuesEvent,2018-08-10 15:12:14+00:00,68423917,adobe-type-tools/psautohint,93914,khaledhosny,2768660,adobe-type-tools,closed,Generated CFF table has undecodable subroutines,"[{'id': 444040779, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NDQwNDA3Nzk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/adobe-type-tools/psautohint/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],4,"Checking the TTX dump of CFF tables generated by psautohint, the `Priviate.Subr` is full of undecoded CharStrings. I think this is because when we convert from CharStrings to bez format we “flatten” the subroutines, and when we convert back the old subroutines become unused and subsequently undecodable.

Not sure if we should do anything here as it probably only increases the file size. I considered just emptying `Priviate.Subr`, but this would break fonts where only a subset of the glyph are hinted (using the `-g` option). I don’t know if there is a way to detect unused subroutines and prune them.",{},{}
