11378,IssuesEvent,2017-02-14 10:44:02+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,321534,mmckerns,2855931,uqfoundation,closed,Can't pickle loggers on python 3,"[{'id': 45530887, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/uqfoundation/dill/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],1,"I recently upgraded from python 2 to 3, and have been having issues with some code I wrote (using pathos multiprocessing). As far as I can tell, the root of the problem has to do with pickling a logger.

Here's a minimal example copied from a [SO question](http://stackoverflow.com/a/29423145/1515212)  that should work and illustrates the problem:

```
>>> class foo:
...    def __init__(self):
...        self.logger = logging.getLogger(""package.foo"")
... 
>>> import dill
>>> import logging
>>> 
>>> f = foo()
>>> _f = dill.dumps(f)  
>>> f_ = dill.loads(_f)
>>> f_.logger
<logging.Logger object at 0x110b1d250>
```
If I run this code verbatim on my system I  get `TypeError: can't pickle _thread.RLock objects`.

