11380,IssuesEvent,2018-07-11 01:02:15+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,12143447,polsar88,2855931,uqfoundation,opened,dill does not restore __name__ attribute of a functools.partial object if set,[],[],0,"```
import dill
import functools

def f():
    pass
f.__name__
Out[56]: 'f'

g = functools.partial(f)
g.__name__ = 'g'
g.__name__
Out[59]: 'g'

h = dill.loads(dill.dumps(g))
hasattr(h, '__name__')
Out[61]: False
```
As you can see, dill does not restore `g`'s `__name__` attribute. Same issue affects `pickle`.",{},{}
