11664,IssuesEvent,2016-05-15 20:14:27+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Top-down SourceRoots scanning does not respect pants_ignore,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"This is because `SourceRoots.all_roots` hand-rolls ignores where it would probably be using a `ProjectTree`.  Some work to untangle `ProjectTree` instantiation from `goal_runner.py` is probably needed first.

One upshot of this is this [jenkins CI failure](http://jenkins.pantsbuild.org/job/pantsbuild/job/pants/branch/master/38/execution/node/426/log/):
```
...
[== 10:39 Installing and testing package pantsbuild.pants.contrib.go-1.1.0-pre0 ... ==]


13:44:41 00:00 [main]
               (To run a reporting server: ./pants server)
13:44:41 00:00   [setup]
13:44:41 00:00     [parse]
               Executing tasks in goals: buildgen -> bootstrap -> imports -> unpack-jars -> deferred-sources -> jvm-platform-validate -> gen -> resolve -> compile -> resources -> test
13:44:42 00:01   [buildgen]
13:44:42 00:01     [go]
                   buildgen.go ignoring targets passed on the command line and re-materializing the complete Go BUILD forest.
FAILURE: Can only BUILD gen for a single Go local sources source root, found:
	.cache/pantsbuild/pants/bin/go/mac/10.10/1.6.2/unpacked/go/src/go
	.home/.cache/pants/bin/go/mac/10.10/1.6.2/unpacked/go/src/go
	contrib/go/examples/src/go


13:44:43 00:02   [complete]
               FAILURE

Failed to install and test package pantsbuild.pants.contrib.go-1.1.0-pre0!

Dry run release failed.

Failed to create pants distributions.
```

Here the default options should be preventing `SourceRoots` from considering `.cache/` or `.home/` dirs:
```
$ ./pants options | grep pants_ignore
pants_ignore = ['.*', 'build-support/*.venv/'] (from CONFIG)
```
",{},{}
11667,IssuesEvent,2016-04-04 18:35:39+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Port `visualizer` out of `examples` and into the Scheduler,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine', 'name': 'engine', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],0,"Currently the `visualizer` is a unique entrypoint for the `examples` package. Consequently, we can only visualize executions that use the tasks defined in the examples package.

Instead, the ""meat"" of visualization should move out of https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/src/python/pants/engine/exp/examples/visualizer.py and into https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/src/python/pants/engine/exp/scheduler.py (or some other module in the root `exp` package), where it can be executed as at any time by an interested caller. The `visualizer` module would then use the logic in the core package to visualize things.

As a reminder: the visualizer is currently executed like:
```
./pants run src/python/pants/engine/exp/examples:viz --   .   list  3rdparty/::
```",{},{}
11668,IssuesEvent,2017-11-21 06:39:23+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,34,nitay,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Building Play Apps,"[{'id': 233931066, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/idea', 'name': 'idea', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 234031381, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/user%20reported', 'name': 'user reported', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],3,"We have a large codebase with lots of scala/python, and also use [Play](https://www.playframework.com/) for our webapps. We'd love to use Pants, but building the Play app is a blocker.

From a cursory scan at very least, Pants would need to:
- compile routes file (twirl) into scala
- compile html templates into scala
- package javascript/css assets. This includes its whole own pipeline (webpack, minify, etc)
- build all those parts together
- add in play's runner (the main entrypoint)
",{},{}
