11687,IssuesEvent,2017-06-29 21:55:37+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,The `-c` form of `--pants-config-files` does not work for options bootstrapping.,"[{'id': 22426646, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 137550486, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/in-progress', 'name': 'in-progress', 'color': '009800', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'jsirois', 'id': 157586, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/157586?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jsirois', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,I discovered this doing ad-hoc testing for #4587 via `./pants -c=pants.cache.ini test.pytest tests/python/pants_test/cache/:cache_setup`. The local cache was not being turned on. The `-c` short form of `--pants-config-files` was added in #4715 but the [`get_config_file_paths`](https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/src/python/pants/option/options_bootstrapper.py#L28-L55) method was not updated to account for this alternate form. Updating that method raises issues since a mild TODO now becomes much more prominent without a refactoring of the options parsing system to ensure we read the global `-c` and not a local one.,{},{}
11722,IssuesEvent,2017-11-27 18:01:34+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Run checkstyle as a standalone step,[],[],4,"Currently, when we run checkstyle it depends on the compile step running.

I think this makes sense in that we don't want to run checkstyle on code that doesn't compile, but sometimes we want to run a quick check of code before we submit a change request.  I'm thinking that we could so something like  `./pants checkstyle-only $(./pants what-changed <sha>)` and have it just check to make sure that files that have changed still pass checkstyle, say in a git pre-commit hook.
",{},{}
