12355,IssuesEvent,2015-08-17 13:24:48+00:00,12407457,Exa-Networks/exabgp,1227755,thomas-mangin,5339170,Exa-Networks,closed,Flowspec redirect to IP not working with XR 5.3.1 ?,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Exa-Networks/exabgp/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],27,"Hi,

I am trying to setup a redirect-to-ip rule from exabgp (3.4.11) to IOS XR 5.3.1 but XR does not seem to receive the appropriate extended communities and so does not redirect the traffic.

ExaBGP log says : 
```
reactor       | Flow added to neighbor 1.2.3.4 local-ip 5.6.7.8 local-as 65500 peer-as 65500 router-id 5.6.7.8 family-allowed in-open : flow destination a.b.c.d/32 next-hop e.f.g.h extended-community redirect-to-nexthop 
which looks fine to me
```
but XR sees: 
```
#show bgp ipv4 flowspec Dest:a.b.c.d/32/48 detail
Fri Jul 17 12:08:29.515 UTC
BGP routing table entry for Dest:a.b.c.d/32/48
NLRI in Hex: 0120c39ab2a3/48
Versions:
  Process           bRIB/RIB  SendTblVer
  Speaker                106         106
    Flags: 0x04001001+0x00000000;
Last Modified: Jul 17 12:08:24.157 for 00:00:05
Paths: (1 available, best #1)
  Not advertised to any peer
  Path #1: Received by speaker 1
  Flags: 0x4000000001060005, import: 0x20
  Not advertised to any peer
  Local
    e.f.g.h (metric 100) from 5.6.7.8 (5.6.7.8)
      Origin IGP, localpref 100, valid, confed-internal, best, group-best
      Received Path ID 0, Local Path ID 1, version 106
```
if I set the same rule locally on XR (with class-map/policy-map), I get almost the same output but with these communities added (and with this it actually redirects traffic) : 
```
      ""Extended community: FLOWSPEC Redirect-IP:0""
```
 I use the following flow syntax in ExaBGP : 
```
""neighbor %s announce flow route { match { destination %s; } then { redirect %s; } }\n""
```
also tried with : 
```
""neighbor %s announce flow route { next-hop e.f.g.h; match { destination %s; } then { redirect-to-nexthop; } }\n""
```
am I forgetting something or are the extended communities attributes not set correctly in exabgp ?
(also tried adding some extended-communities [ xxx:yyy ] and those where properly advertised to XR)

thanks
Mik",{},{}
