12619,IssuesEvent,2018-01-08 17:08:52+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,16001974,DeNeutoy,5667695,allenai,opened,Make Span F1 match perl script exactly for SRL model,[],[],0,"The Span based F1 metric doesn't exactly match the perl script for evaluating the SRL model. I think this is because the perl script treats continuation and reference spans (C-B-TAG, R-B-TAG) as part of the same span as what they are continuing or referencing, whereas the allennlp metric treats these as separate spans. ",{},{}
12630,IssuesEvent,2018-07-18 20:56:03+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,954798,schmmd,5667695,allenai,closed,Broken link in tutorial,[],[],0,"**Describe the bug**
The tutorial `using_as_a_library_pt1.md` has a broken link. It's meant to link to `using_as_a_library_pt2.md` but instead links to `making_predictions_and_creating_a_demo.md`. 

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior
1. Go to [part 1](https://github.com/allenai/allennlp/blob/master/tutorials/getting_started/using_as_a_library_pt1.md) of the using as a library tutorial page.
2. Scroll down to the very bottom.
3. Click on **Making Predictions and Creating a Demo**
4. 404 error

**Expected behavior**
The link should instead take you to [part 2](https://github.com/allenai/allennlp/blob/master/tutorials/getting_started/using_as_a_library_pt2.md) of the tutorial.
",{},{}
12643,IssuesEvent,2015-12-23 16:23:38+00:00,13512018,python-diamond/Diamond,1193646,klank4135,5668086,python-diamond,opened,Unable to Disable DEBUG Log on Diamond,[],[],0,"The only way I've found to actually disable (verbose) logging, diamond.conf

[server]
# handlers = diamond.handler.graphite.GraphiteHandler, diamond.handler.archive.ArchiveHandler
handlers = diamond.handler.graphite.GraphiteHandler

A possible way to logging is: log WARN+ERROR for system level diamond process things ""WARNING: could not load extra python module libsomething"", and ERROR for metrics ""ERROR: could not connect to mysql to gather metrics"".  but *not* to log every single metric gathered... that's just way too verbose and not useful, except during debugging",{},{}
