I think `globus endpoint is-activated` is still useful/good. Maybe we can discuss the future fates of these commands post-GlobusWorld and see if some kind of merging is reasonable.
Meantimes, we need to resurrect an old command: `globus endpoint activate`
This has PM signoff, so we should go ahead and implement.

Proposed Usage:
```
globus endpoint activate ENDPOINT_ID \
  -U/--myproxy-username USERNAME \
  -P/--myproxy-password PASSWORD
```

- Should attempt autoactivation if no credentials are given
- Only needs to support autoactivation and myproxy activation (for now)
- Helptext should note that commandline creds are for ""MyProxy"", not ""OAuth for MyProxy""
- `-U` requires `-P` and vice-versa
- Optional: allow `globus config set cli.default_myproxy_username USERNAME` to set a default for `-U`",{},{}
