KeyError: 'menuinst-1.0.4-py27_0.tar.bz2'
```

This issue effectively prevents us from using anaconda offline as our company policy prevents outside access from internal apps.

Is it possible to tell conda not to use the internet? Surely it has all the information it needs to in order to clone the root environment?
