13475,IssuesEvent,2017-11-03 02:52:26+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,10146011,JasonRShaver,6844498,Azure,closed,generate-sas generate useless SAS if permission and expiry are not given. ,"[{'id': 418968915, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Discussion', 'name': 'Discussion', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 418939315, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Storage', 'name': 'Storage', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],3,"The only required parameters in blob generate-sas command are container name and blob name. When other parameters are omitted, the result is useless. The SAS token can do nothing because neither permission or expiry are represented in the token.

