13483,IssuesEvent,2016-10-22 23:53:30+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,116461,lostintangent,6844498,Azure,opened,[ACR] Repository list command doesn't support table output,[],[],0,"Running `acr repository list`, while the CLI is configured to use table output (which is the new default?), outputs the following error:

`Table output unavailable. Use the --query option to specify an appropriate query. Use --debug for more info.`

If I append `--query ""repositories""`, then the table output will work, so I have to at list give the CLI props for the nice error message :) However, it's non-ideal to need to view the JSON output of the command, in order to understand the schema, and then add a `--query` flag in order to ""pluck"" the repositories list out of the returned object. 

Maybe I'm doing something wrong, but I've not encountered another list command in the CLI that didn't naturally support table output, so it would be cool if `acr repository list` did as well.",{},{}
