14148,IssuesEvent,2017-08-14 00:40:00+00:00,1199632,schematics/schematics,142916,alexhayes,7866441,schematics,opened,Models can no longer be pickled,[],[],0,"It appears that somewhere between version `2.0.0a1` and `2.0.1` models can no longer be pickled.

```python
import pickle
from schematics.models import Model
from schematics.types import IntType

class Foo(Model):
    bar = IntType()

f = Foo(dict(bar=1))

pickle.dumps(f)
```

Results in: `TypeError: can't pickle mappingproxy objects`

Note that I attempted to do a `git bisect start HEAD a8249f1 --` on master but there are many commits that are essentially broken thus bisect doesn't appear possible. Even if I modify the above script to return `125` if we can't determine the exit code (ie.. for issues like `cannot import name 'ComputedType'` and `No module named 'schematics.inspection'`) essentially git bisect gets to a point where there are only skipped commits left to test (ie.. dead end).

With a bit more digging I could ascertain that it was definitely broken by 65f3d95 and was good in b90990a so somewhere between those two it was broken.

This is perhaps related to #474.",{},{}
