14251,IssuesEvent,2017-03-02 22:16:05+00:00,24375248,blockstack/blockstack-core,459947,jcnelson,8165984,blockstack,closed,Automate publishing of fast-sync images,"[{'id': 269179581, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/blockstack/blockstack-core/labels/deployment', 'name': 'deployment', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 156558119, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/blockstack/blockstack-core/labels/feature', 'name': 'feature', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'jcnelson', 'id': 459947, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/459947?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jcnelson', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"We need to automate the publishing of Blockstack state i.e., (a) Blockstack Core snapshots, (b) the Atlas DB, and (c) zonefiles for fast-sync mode. 

We decided on the following process: 

- We'll publish new state files (images) every 24 hours. So a new node using fast-sync can be at most 24 hours behind the latest state. 
- We'll get signatures from at least 3 Blockstack Core developers on the state files.
- We'll have a cron job that automates the publishing of these images.",{},{}
14258,IssuesEvent,2017-03-23 15:36:16+00:00,24375248,blockstack/blockstack-core,669932,muneeb-ali,8165984,blockstack,opened,Spawning a new API process ,"[{'id': 269175553, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/blockstack/blockstack-core/labels/api', 'name': 'api', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 131873975, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/blockstack/blockstack-core/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'jcnelson', 'id': 459947, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/459947?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jcnelson', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jcnelson/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Right now we use sys.executable for spawning a new process [in rpc.py](https://github.com/blockstack/blockstack-core/blob/master/blockstack_client/rpc.py#L3508). This works as long as we're invoking it from Python. But other executables, e.g., uWSGI, can also end up calling such functions. 

We could either explicitly check for Python and read the correct path some other way e.g., PYTHONPATH or now spawn a new process.

I had a discussion with @jcnelson about this earlier and he seemed to prefer the ""not spawning a new process"" route. 

Not including this for v0.14.2.",{},{}
