14582,IssuesEvent,2016-02-29 21:27:52+00:00,45062555,F5Networks/f5-common-python,640955,zancas,8935905,F5Networks,closed,Create an exists() method for resource objects.,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/f5-common-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/f5-common-python/labels/feature%20request', 'name': 'feature request', 'color': 'bfd4f2'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/f5-common-python/labels/refactor', 'name': 'refactor', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],0,"A very common thing for the projects using this SDK to do is to check for the existence of an object.  While this can be done by doing something like the following it is a bit painful for such a common operation by users:

```python
try:
    pool = bigip.ltm.pools.pool.load(partition='Common', name='mypool')
except HTTPError as err:
   if err.response.status_code == 404:
       pool = bigip.ltm.pools.pool.create(partition='Common', name='mypool')
   else:
       raise
```

I think it would be a lost more useful for our users to be able to do the following to hide the `try`/`except` above:
```python
if not bigip.ltm.pools.pool.exists(partition='Common', name='mypool'):
    pool = bigip.ltm.pools.pool.create(partition='Common', name='mypool')
```",{},{}
14583,IssuesEvent,2018-05-19 05:28:24+00:00,45062555,F5Networks/f5-common-python,46956,caphrim007,8935905,F5Networks,opened,make gtm pools support slashes,[],[],0,"GTM pools support slashes, but the sdk is preventing them. Fix this",{},{}
14601,IssuesEvent,2018-06-16 03:17:30+00:00,1151051,django-oscar/django-oscar,160227,solarissmoke,9057806,django-oscar,closed,Forms need to be loaded dynamically by ALL views modules,[],[],1,"### Issue Summary

Dashboard flatpages forms are not loaded dynamically into the respective view module, but directly imported. This is also true for the reviews forms.

### Steps to Reproduce

1. Override an existing form in your own `dashboard.pages.forms`
2. Navigate through your dashboard to the view which should show said form
3. Cry?

I'm not really sure why all the other dashboard apps dynamically load forms using `get_class`, and yet `pages` and `reviews` import them directly. This makes it difficult to override those forms, since we now require a view override as well as a form override.

These two view modules _really_ should import their respective forms using `get_class`, unless there's an extremely good reason to favor direct import.

### Technical details

* Python version: 3.6.4
* Django version: 1.11.13
* Oscar version: 1.5.4

### Related issues
#2209 ""Needed documentation to ovewrite/modificate dashboard forms""
This issue's primary comment suggests that any dashboard app can be overridden and its forms modified, which is largely, but not completely, true.
",{},{}
