14994,IssuesEvent,2017-10-16 15:34:53+00:00,552926,django-ckeditor/django-ckeditor,4029388,tisdall,9961418,django-ckeditor,opened,GIF thumbnail issue,[],[],0,"Okay...  this is a little convoluted so I'll start from the beginning...

I was using version 5.2.2 and when a user tried uploading a .gif I got the following exception (I'm just included the parts related to this lib):
```
  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/ckeditor_uploader/views.py"", line 66, in post
    self._create_thumbnail_if_needed(backend, saved_path)

  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/ckeditor_uploader/views.py"", line 89, in _create_thumbnail_if_needed
    backend.create_thumbnail(saved_path)

  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/ckeditor_uploader/image/pillow_backend.py"", line 45, in create_thumbnail
    imagefit.save(thumbnail_io, format=file_format)

  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/PIL/Image.py"", line 1826, in save
    save_handler(self, fp, filename)

  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/PIL/GifImagePlugin.py"", line 458, in _save
    _write_single_frame(im, fp, palette)

  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/PIL/GifImagePlugin.py"", line 378, in _write_single_frame
    _write_local_header(fp, im, (0, 0), flags)

  File ""/data/virtualenv/default/lib/python2.7/site-packages/PIL/GifImagePlugin.py"", line 483, in _write_local_header
    transparency = int(transparency)

TypeError: int() argument must be a string or a number, not 'tuple'
```

I checked to see if there was a new version so I thought I'd try that to see if the issue was solved.  I installed 5.3.0 and after putting in a hack to get around #411 I found that I no longer got the exception.  However, I also found that I no longer got a thumbnail, either.

It seems that #351 [added the following code](https://github.com/AliYmn/django-ckeditor/blob/master/ckeditor_uploader/views.py#L67) that stops thumbnails for GIFs:
```
        if(str(saved_path).split('.')[1].lower() != 'gif'):
            self._create_thumbnail_if_needed(backend, saved_path)
```

So, the bug wasn't fixed but a new bug stopped the old bug from happening.  Also, [as stated in #351 a different method should be used to determine the file type](https://github.com/django-ckeditor/django-ckeditor/pull/351#issuecomment-277532747).  There doesn't appear to be any explanation in #351 why thumbnails for GIF is disabled, but I suspect they ran into the same issue I did.",{},{}
