I had a look in my debugger - think it's something to do with that some of the field names are the same? Perhaps something to do with how ret is constructed here: https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/blob/dev/marshmallow/schema.py#L729

Let me know if I'm missing something in my config somewhere!",{},{}
15172,IssuesEvent,2016-08-04 02:48:07+00:00,14284859,marshmallow-code/marshmallow,2379650,sloria,10334301,marshmallow-code,closed,Could How To Run Tests Be Added To the Readme?,[],[],1,"Hi all, I'm loving Marshmallow and would love to contribute. I have but one issue and that is getting the test suite running on my machine. Looking at the README, there is no contributing section outlining how to actually run the tests, like most libraries do. Examples of other projects that have clear contributing sections outlining how to run the tests are [Flask](https://github.com/pallets/flask), [httpie](https://github.com/jkbrzt/httpie/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.rst), and, everyone's favorite, [Requests[(https://github.com/kennethreitz/requests#how-to-contribute) (though he doesn't say explictly how to run tests, but that's whatever).

Thoughts? Also, how do you run the tests? All I'm getting is flake checking external dependencies for style.",{},{}
15211,IssuesEvent,2015-10-20 22:21:13+00:00,40094312,pyserial/pyserial,10556012,zsquareplusc,10537924,pyserial,closed,Raise TimeoutError on timeout,[],[],3,"When I set a timeout like this:

    ser = serial.Serial('/dev/ttyS1', 19200, timeout=1)

pyserial just retries reads like this:

    character = ser.read()

I need to be able to know, when the read has timed out to resend my last message. Please raise a TimeoutError, so I can use pyserial like this:

    while True:
        try:
            character = console.read()
        except TimeoutError:
            console.write(message)
            character = console.read()

I think that it is unpythonic to silently drop errors like a timeout. When a user of pyserial invokes a read(), the expected outcome is that it returns the data that has been read. So hitting the timeout is an error.",{},{}
