15911,IssuesEvent,2018-06-11 12:58:08+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,3453847,zardus,12520807,angr,opened,Quick project: give reasonable names to symbolic registers,"[{'id': 245054965, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwyNDUwNTQ5NjU=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/angr/angr/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}, {'id': 674590248, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NzQ1OTAyNDg=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/angr/angr/labels/project', 'name': 'project', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],0,"When a register is accessed (`state.regs.rax`) and nothing was previously written there, angr creates a new symbolic variable and names it something stupid using the VEX register file offset (specifically, something like `reg_10_0_64`). However, here, we have enough information (from `state.arch.register_names` and `state.arch.registers`) to figure out what register was being accessed, and we should really create a name like `reg_rax_0_64` or just `rax_0_64`.

This can be done in: https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/state_plugins/symbolic_memory.py#L438",{},{}
