16269,IssuesEvent,2017-07-12 04:56:31+00:00,30212825,Amber-MD/pytraj,4451957,hainm,13525542,Amber-MD,reopened,rmsf: API reference page missing? per-residue?,[],[],19,"There is a tutorial on using pt.rmsf() on trajectories (http://amber-md.github.io/pytraj/latest/tutorials/rmsf.html), which shows how to perform the analysis on all atoms.  Instead of performing the calculation on a per-atom basis, I'd like to do it on a per-residue basis — but I could not find the corresponding API reference page to figure out how to do this.",{},{}
16272,IssuesEvent,2018-06-11 22:21:05+00:00,30212825,Amber-MD/pytraj,13418175,lacoperon,13525542,Amber-MD,opened,Explained Variance for PCA,[],[],0,"Hi there,

I found myself (for some MD calculations) implementing mostly trivial code which calculates the proportion of the variance explained by each principal component derived from pytraj's PCA function. 

Given that this is a common use case (and that some might find it hard to translate eigenvalue terminology to variance numerically), would it be worthwhile implementing this as a function within pytraj? I could very easily do a quick efficient version of this using numpy and do a pull request -- just was wondering whether or not it would be worthwhile.

Thanks,
- Elliot",{},{}
