The reason is, as I assume, that the R200 has no FishEye mode, since this is only available since SR300.
Uncommenting the equivalent three lines of code in the file and compiling it, returns another exception, what might sound more reasonable to track down the cause to the lacks of R200:

`rs::error was thrown when calling rs_start_source(device:0x830e30, source:ALL):
    motion-tracking is not supported by this device`

I would like to recommend an integration of a condition that informs the user, that this can't be done with R200. Saves some time. :)
",{},{}
