16571,IssuesEvent,2018-08-16 20:33:03+00:00,92238803,openai/baselines,459819,pimdh,14957082,openai,closed,Run script fails on Classic Control,[],[],0,"The MountainCar env does not work with the new run script.

Running: `python -m baselines.run --alg=deepq --env=MountainCar-v0 --num_timesteps=1e6`

Results in exception:
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "".../lib/python3.6/runpy.py"", line 193, in _run_module_as_main
    ""__main__"", mod_spec)
  File "".../lib/python3.6/runpy.py"", line 85, in _run_code
    exec(code, run_globals)
  File "".../openai-baselines/baselines/run.py"", line 230, in <module>
    main()
  File "".../openai-baselines/baselines/run.py"", line 209, in main
    model, _ = train(args, extra_args)
  File "".../openai-baselines/baselines/run.py"", line 56, in train
    env = build_env(args)
  File "".../openai-baselines/baselines/run.py"", line 134, in build_env
    return env
```
This is because here https://github.com/openai/baselines/blob/master/baselines/run.py#L126 it does `env_type == 'classic'`, while MountainCar has `env_type == 'classic_control'`. Replacing both instances of `'classic'` with `'classic_control'` in `run.py` resolves the issue. Shall I file a PR?
",{},{}
