17746,IssuesEvent,2018-02-11 10:23:51+00:00,120933363,gisaia/ARLAS-server,9483289,elouanKeryell-Even,20204404,gisaia,opened,Filters: add `when` as a filter,[],[],0,"In gitlab by @sylvaingaudan on Aug 8, 2017, 14:07

Use `when` in the filters to retain data based on the timestamp:
- `last_hour` : data with timestamp within now and now-1h
- `today` : data with timestamp within the current day
- `yesterday` : data with timestamp within the yesterday
- `last_24h` : data with timestamp within now and now-24h
- `this_week` : this week
- `last_7days` : data with timestamp within now and now-7days
- `this_month` : this week
- `last_30days` : data with timestamp within now and now-30days
- `last_60days` : data with timestamp within now and now-60days
- `last_90days` : data with timestamp within now and now-90days
- `last_365days` : data with timestamp within now and now-365days
- `this_year` : this year

Use a enum for `when` values.",{},{}
