18019,IssuesEvent,2018-05-27 00:55:54+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,249517,robertnishihara,22125274,ray-project,closed,Memory Usage,[],[],18,"I've been attempting to use Ray for some reinforcement learning applications. When I have run multiple agents (implemented as ray Actors so that they train in parallel), the memory used by the driver quickly reaches nearly the memory of the computer I'm using (8GB). I suspect that this is due to the object store serializing the arguments of all of my calls to the agents' train functions, and I was wondering whether there was a way to remove objects if they will not be read again, or choose not to keep certain function arguments after they have been read once.

Thanks for any help.",{},{}
18051,IssuesEvent,2018-08-24 23:26:47+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,14922,ericl,22125274,ray-project,opened,[rllib] Multi-gpu / AsyncReplay support for multi-agent,[],[],0,"
### Describe the problem

Currently multi-gpu PPO and Ape-X don't support multi-agent. This is relatively straightforward for fix:
