18305,IssuesEvent,2017-09-22 15:30:12+00:00,34138622,jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets,192614,jasongrout,25869250,jupyter-widgets,closed,conda install ipywidgets doesn't install the jupyter-js-widgets anymore,[],[],8,"According to the [documentation](http://ipywidgets.readthedocs.io/en/stable/user_install.html#with-conda), running ""conda install -c conda-forge ipywidgets"" should install and enable the extension.
That's not the case with the latest release:

```
$ docker run --rm -it jupyter/minimal-notebook bash
jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ conda install --yes ipywidgets
Fetching package metadata ...........
Solving package specifications: .

Package plan for installation in environment /opt/conda:

The following NEW packages will be INSTALLED:

    ipywidgets:         7.0.1-py_2 conda-forge
    widgetsnbextension: 3.0.3-py_1 conda-forge

widgetsnbexten 100% |###########################################################################################| Time: 0:00:01 810.71 kB/s
ipywidgets-7.0 100% |###########################################################################################| Time: 0:00:00  24.18 MB/s
jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ jupyter nbextension list
Known nbextensions:
  config dir: /opt/conda/etc/jupyter/nbconfig
    notebook section
      jupyter-js-widgets/extension  enabled
      - Validating: problems found:
        - require?  X jupyter-js-widgets/extension
jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ ls /opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions
ls: cannot access '/opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions': No such file or directory
jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ find /opt/conda -name jupyter-js-widgets
```
jupyter-js-widgets is not installed. I had to run:

```
jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ jupyter nbextension install --py widgetsnbextension --sys-prefix
Installing /opt/conda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/widgetsnbextension/static -> jupyter-js-widgets
Making directory: /opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions/jupyter-js-widgets/
Copying: /opt/conda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/widgetsnbextension/static/extension.js -> /opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions/jupyter-js-widgets/extension.js
Copying: /opt/conda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/widgetsnbextension/static/extension.js.map -> /opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions/jupyter-js-widgets/extension.js.map
- Validating: OK

    To initialize this nbextension in the browser every time the notebook (or other app) loads:

          jupyter nbextension enable widgetsnbextension --py --sys-prefix

jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ find /opt/conda -name jupyter-js-widgets
/opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions/jupyter-js-widgets
jovyan@c3094235e935:~$ ls /opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions
jupyter-js-widgets
```

It was working fine with widgetsnbextension=3.0.2:

```
$ docker run --rm -it jupyter/minimal-notebook bash
jovyan@9803a2692ac4:~$ conda install --yes ipywidgets widgetsnbextension=3.0.2
Fetching package metadata ...........
Solving package specifications: .

Package plan for installation in environment /opt/conda:

The following NEW packages will be INSTALLED:

    ipywidgets:         7.0.1-py_2   conda-forge
    widgetsnbextension: 3.0.2-py36_0 conda-forge

widgetsnbexten 100% |####################################################################################################| Time: 0:00:01   1.34 MB/s
ipywidgets-7.0 100% |####################################################################################################| Time: 0:00:00  24.51 MB/s
jovyan@9803a2692ac4:~$ jupyter nbextension list
Known nbextensions:
  config dir: /opt/conda/etc/jupyter/nbconfig
    notebook section
      jupyter-js-widgets/extension  enabled
      - Validating: OK
jovyan@9803a2692ac4:~$ ls /opt/conda/share/jupyter/nbextensions/
jupyter-js-widgets
```

It looks like a regression in widgetsnbextension 3.0.3
",{},{}
