18391,IssuesEvent,2018-03-09 00:46:41+00:00,71482397,Parsl/parsl,5114833,annawoodard,26490185,Parsl,opened,Add linting for docstrings,[],[],0,"Now that we have an awesome setup due to @yadudoc that plugs code linting into Travis, I think it makes sense to add linting for our docstrings. It can be done via:

```
pep257 --ignore=D100,D101,D102,D103,D104
```

Or if you want more info:
```
pep257 --ignore=D100,D101,D102,D103,D104  --explain --source
```
The full list of errors can be found [here](http://pep257.readthedocs.io/en/latest/error_codes.html). Resolving this issue should also include fixing the current things pep257 is complaining about. I can volunteer for this, since I'm currently going through the code to get familiar with it.",{},{}
18394,IssuesEvent,2018-03-08 16:24:02+00:00,71482397,Parsl/parsl,5114833,annawoodard,26490185,Parsl,opened,Remove duplicated tutorial,[],[],0,Having two files with the same name but different cases does not play nice on case-insensitive filesystems (like OS X). The duplicated tutorial [here](https://github.com/Parsl/parsl/tree/master/docs/quick) should be removed.,{},{}
