18468,IssuesEvent,2017-08-27 11:45:59+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,2807888,whummer,28732122,localstack,closed,Bug: install_amazon_kinesis_libs() failure,"[{'id': 468888569, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/localstack/localstack/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 571606741, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/localstack/localstack/labels/installation', 'name': 'installation', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}, {'id': 577928994, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/localstack/localstack/labels/priority-high', 'name': 'priority-high', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}]",[],1,"I’m experiencing a strange inconsistency between two systems, attempting to run localstack under virtualenv:

1. Mac OS X 10.12.5, Java 1.8.0_121, Python 3.6.0, `virtualenv -p python3 .venv`
2. Mac OS X 10.12.5, Java 1.8.0_144, Python 3.6.1, `python -m venv .venv`

On the second system _only_, `install_amazon_kinesis_libs()` fails to run. I’ve narrowed the problem down to a missing set of jars in the `amazon_kclpy` package: they’re present on system 1, and absent on system 2. I can’t determine why there’s an inconsistency, how or why to get system 2 to install the jars, or why they’re needed. I’m not using Kinesis, so I’m able to make progress by commenting out the call to `install_amazon_kinesis_libs()` in `install_components()`.",{},{}
