18734,IssuesEvent,2018-07-06 15:37:18+00:00,3845895,fastavro/fastavro,6951699,scottbelden,40203918,fastavro,opened,file_reader isn't doing anything useful when the writer and reader schemas match,[],[],0,"In https://github.com/fastavro/fastavro/commit/14f5833ff2e6d05a65ebfb8e5d69f9d5da511852#diff-32e7cfc438f3c071ebde3e0295f40985 a small check was done to see if the writer and reader schemas match. If they do, the reader is supposed to be set to `None` to prevent the `match_schema` checks. However, here: https://github.com/fastavro/fastavro/blob/5729d04297276ee0e01cf02ef7c7c4cd1779746a/fastavro/_read.pyx#L682 and here: https://github.com/fastavro/fastavro/blob/5729d04297276ee0e01cf02ef7c7c4cd1779746a/fastavro/_read_py.py#L604 we set `reader_schema = None` when we should be setting `self.reader_schema = None`.

A few tests need to be updated for this to be fixed. We might need to do something like create a new `_internal_reader_schema` that gets set to `None` while the normal `reader_schema` attribute is still set to the real schema so that `reader_schema` attribute still continues to hold the schema that is passed in.",{},{}
